### ============================================================
### ASSIGNMENT MODULE — API LIFECYCLE TESTS
### File: backend/api-tests/assignment.http
### ============================================================
### HOW TO USE:
### 1. Install REST Client extension in VS Code
### 2. Run: npm run dev
### 3. Run Block 0 first to get your seed IDs
### 4. Paste IDs into @variables below
### 5. Send each request top to bottom
### ============================================================


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 0 — GET SEED IDs
### ============================================================


### 0.1 — Get all users (find manager, worker, admin, inactive user IDs)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/users
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 0.2 — Get all projects (copy a project ID)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 0.3 — Create a task to run assignment tests on (expect 201)
# @name testTask
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/projects/PASTE_PROJECT_UUID_HERE/tasks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Assignment Test Task",
  "priority": "medium",
  "due_date": "2026-08-01",
  "created_by": "PASTE_MANAGER_UUID_HERE"
}

###

### ✏️ PASTE IDs here after running 0.1, 0.2, 0.3
@projectId  = PASTE_PROJECT_UUID_HERE
@managerId  = PASTE_MANAGER_UUID_HERE
@workerId   = PASTE_WORKER_UUID_HERE
@adminId    = PASTE_ADMIN_UUID_HERE
@taskId     = PASTE_TASK_UUID_HERE

### NOTE: If you have a second worker in seed data, paste here
@worker2Id  = PASTE_WORKER2_UUID_HERE


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 1 — CREATE (Assign worker to task)
### ============================================================


### 1.1 — ✅ Assign worker to task (expect 201)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{workerId}}",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.2 — ✅ Assign a second worker to same task (expect 201)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{worker2Id}}",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.3 — ❌ NEGATIVE: duplicate assignment — same worker again (expect 409)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{workerId}}",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: assign an admin (not a worker — expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{adminId}}",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.5 — ❌ NEGATIVE: assign a manager (not a worker — expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{managerId}}",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.6 — ❌ NEGATIVE: user_id does not exist (expect 404)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.7 — ❌ NEGATIVE: assigned_by does not exist (expect 404)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{workerId}}",
  "assigned_by": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"
}

###

### 1.8 — ❌ NEGATIVE: user_id is not a valid UUID (expect 400 from Zod)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "not-a-uuid",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.9 — ❌ NEGATIVE: assigned_by is not a valid UUID (expect 400 from Zod)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{workerId}}",
  "assigned_by": "not-a-uuid"
}

###

### 1.10 — ❌ NEGATIVE: missing user_id field (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###

### 1.11 — ❌ NEGATIVE: missing assigned_by field (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{workerId}}"
}

###

### 1.12 — ❌ NEGATIVE: completely empty body (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 1.13 — ❌ NEGATIVE: task does not exist (expect 404)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{workerId}}",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 2 — READ
### ============================================================


### 2.1 — ✅ Get all assignments for the task (expect 200, array with assignee details)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.2 — ✅ Get the task itself — verify assignees array is populated (expect 200)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2.3 — ❌ NEGATIVE: task does not exist (expect 404)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 3 — ASSIGN TO DONE TASK
### First move the task to done, then try to assign
### ============================================================


### 3.1 — Move task to in_progress (status machine step 1)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_progress"
}

###

### 3.2 — Move task to in_review (status machine step 2)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "in_review"
}

###

### 3.3 — Move task to done (status machine step 3)
PATCH http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/status
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "done"
}

###

### 3.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: assign worker to a done task (expect 400)
POST http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "user_id": "{{workerId}}",
  "assigned_by": "{{managerId}}"
}

###


### ============================================================
### BLOCK 4 — DELETE (Remove assignment)
### ============================================================


### 4.1 — ✅ Remove worker from task (expect 204 — empty body)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments/{{workerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.2 — ✅ Verify worker is no longer in assignments (expect 200, worker gone)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.3 — ❌ NEGATIVE: remove same assignment again (expect 404)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments/{{workerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.4 — ❌ NEGATIVE: remove assignment for non-existent user on task (expect 404)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.5 — ❌ NEGATIVE: task does not exist (expect 404)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/assignments/{{workerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.6 — ✅ Remove second worker from task (expect 204)
DELETE http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments/{{worker2Id}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.7 — ✅ Verify assignments list is now empty (expect 200, empty array)
GET http://localhost:3001/api/v1/tasks/{{taskId}}/assignments
Content-Type: application/json

###


